modules.description: Encodes and decodes data using Base58 encoding, handling arbitrary byte sequences and strings. It processes unsigned integers and byte arrays, converting them to and from Base58 representations. This is useful for generating human-readable identifiers in blockchain applications.

Encodes and decodes integers and big integers into Base58 strings using customizable alphabets, and decodes Base58 strings into numeric types. It supports specific alphabets like Flickr and Bitcoin for consistent encoding. Used to generate short, URL-safe representations of numeric identifiers in distributed systems.
